{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The style layer’s predicate."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSPredicate","text":"NSPredicate"},{"kind":"text","text":" * "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"predicate"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the style layer’s predicate to include only the features in the source","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layer that satisfy a condition that you define. If the style layer initially","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"comes from the style, its predicate corresponds to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"filter"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"property in the style JSON.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See the “"},{"type":"text","text":"Predicates and Expressions"},{"type":"text","text":"”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"guide for details about the predicate syntax supported by this class."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Example","anchor":"Example"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To filter the layer to include only the features whose ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"index"},{"text":" attribute is 5","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or 10 and whose ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ele"},{"text":" attribute is at least 1,500, you could create an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSCompoundPredicate"},{"text":" along these lines:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing